===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|voice}}, {{m|enm|voys}}, {{m|enm|vois}}, borrowed from {{der|en|xno|[[voiz]], [[voys]], [[voice]]}}, {{der|en|fro|[[vois]], [[voiz]]}} (Modern {{cog|fr|voix}}), from {{der|en|la|vōcem}}, accusative form of {{m|la|vōx|t=voice}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*wṓkʷs}}, [[root noun]] from {{m|ine-pro|*wekʷ-|t=to utter, speak}}. Cognate with {{cog|sa|वाच्}}, {{cog|grc|ὄψ}}, {{cog|fa|آواز|tr=âvâz}}. Displaced native {{cog|enm|steven|t=voice}}, from {{cog|ang|stefn}} (see {{l|en|steven}}). Compare {{m|en|advocate}}, {{m|en|advowson}}, {{m|en|avouch}}, {{m|en|convoke}}, {{m|en|epic}}, {{m|en|vocal}}, {{m|en|vouch}}, {{m|en|vowel}}.

